Melee Weapon Attack: +6 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: [[/damage 2d8 + @mod type=slashing average=true]] damage.

The [[lookup @name]] attacks with its [[lookup @item.name]].

The hag covers herself and anything she is wearing or carrying with a magical &Reference[ill]{illusion} that makes her look like another creature of her general size and &Reference[humanoid]{humanoid} shape. The &Reference[ill]{illusion} ends if the hag takes a bonus action to end it or if she dies.

The changes wrought by this effect fail to hold up to physical inspection. For example, the hag could appear to have smooth skin, but someone touching her would feel her rough flesh. Otherwise, a creature must take an action to visually inspect the &Reference[ill]{illusion} and succeed on a DC 20 &Reference[int]{Intelligence} (&Reference[inv]{Investigation}) check to discern that the hag is disguised.

The [[lookup @name]] uses [[lookup @item.name]].

The hag magically turns &Reference[invisible]{invisible} until she attacks or casts a spell, or until her &Reference[concentration]{concentration} ends (as if concentrating on a spell). While &Reference[invisible]{invisible}, she leaves no physical evidence of her passage, so she can be tracked only by magic. Any equipment she wears or carries is &Reference[invisible]{invisible} with her.

The [[lookup @name]] uses [[lookup @item.name]].

Amphibious. The hag can breathe air and water.

The [[lookup @name]] uses [[lookup @item.name]].

Innate Spellcasting. The hag's innate spellcasting ability is &Reference[cha]{Charisma} (spell save DC 12). She can innately cast the following spells, requiring no &Reference[material]{material} components:

At will: dancing lights, minor &Reference[ill]{illusion}, vicious mockery

The [[lookup @name]] uses [[lookup @item.name]].

Mimicry. The hag can mimic animal sounds and &Reference[humanoid]{humanoid} voices. A creature that hears the sounds can tell they are imitations with a successful DC 14 &Reference[wis]{Wisdom} (&Reference[ins]{Insight}) check.

The [[lookup @name]] uses [[lookup @item.name]].

You create up to four torch-sized lights within range, making them appear as torches, lanterns, or glowing orbs that hover in the air for the duration. You can also combine the four lights into one glowing vaguely &Reference[humanoid]{humanoid} form of Medium size. Whichever form you choose, each light sheds dim light in a 10-foot radius.

As a bonus action on your turn, you can move the lights up to 60 feet to a new spot within range. A light must be within 20 feet of another light created by this spell, and a light winks out if it exceeds the spell's range.

macro.name: Dancing Lights

description.value:
You create a sound or an image of an object within range that lasts for the duration. The &Reference[ill]{illusion} also ends if you dismiss it as an action or cast this spell again.

If you create a sound, its volume can range from a whisper to a scream. It can be your voice, someone else's voice, a lion's roar, a beating of drums, or any other sound you choose. The sound continues unabated throughout the duration, or you can make discrete sounds at different times before the spell ends.

If you create an image of an object--such as a chair, muddy footprints, or a small chest--it must be no larger than a 5-foot &Reference[cube]{cube}. The image can't create sound, light, smell, or any other sensory effect. Physical interaction with the image reveals it to be an &Reference[ill]{illusion}, because things can pass through it.

If a creature uses its action to examine the sound or image, the creature can determine that it is an &Reference[ill]{illusion} with a successful &Reference[int]{Intelligence} (&Reference[inv]{Investigation}) check against your spell save DC. If a creature discerns the &Reference[ill]{illusion} for what it is, the &Reference[ill]{illusion} becomes faint to the creature.

You unleash a string of insults laced with subtle enchantments at a creature you can see within range. If the target can hear you (though it need not understand you), it must succeed on a &Reference[wis]{Wisdom} saving throw or take 1d4 &Reference[psychic]{psychic} damage and have disadvantage on the next attack roll it makes before the end of its next turn.

This spell's damage increases by 1d4 when you reach 5th level (2d4), 11th level (3d4), and 17th level (4d4).
